{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"About four years ago, the New Yorker published an article"},{"time":3000,"text":"about a cache of dodo bones that was found"},{"time":5000,"text":"in a pit on the island of Mauritius."},{"time":8000,"text":"Now, the island of Mauritius is a small island"},{"time":10000,"text":"off the east coast of Madagascar"},{"time":13000,"text":"in the Indian Ocean, and it is the place"},{"time":15000,"text":"where the dodo bird was discovered"},{"time":18000,"text":"and extinguished, all within about 150 years."},{"time":21000,"text":"Everyone was very excited about this archaeological find,"},{"time":24000,"text":"because it meant that they might finally be able"},{"time":26000,"text":"to assemble a single dodo skeleton."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28000,"text":"See, while museums all over the world"},{"time":30000,"text":"have dodo skeletons in their collection, nobody --"},{"time":33000,"text":"not even the actual Natural History Museum"},{"time":35000,"text":"on the island of Mauritius -- has a skeleton that's made"},{"time":37000,"text":"from the bones of a single dodo."},{"time":40000,"text":"Well, this isn't exactly true."},{"time":42000,"text":"The fact is, is that the British Museum"},{"time":44000,"text":"had a complete specimen of a dodo in their collection"},{"time":46000,"text":"up until the 18th century --"},{"time":48000,"text":"it was actually mummified, skin and all --"},{"time":50000,"text":"but in a fit of space-saving zeal,"},{"time":52000,"text":"they actually cut off the head and they cut off the feet"},{"time":54000,"text":"and they burned the rest in a bonfire."},{"time":57000,"text":"If you go look at their website today,"},{"time":59000,"text":"they'll actually list these specimens, saying,"},{"time":61000,"text":"the rest was lost in a fire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64000,"text":"Not quite the whole truth. Anyway."},{"time":67000,"text":"The frontispiece of this article was this photo,"},{"time":69000,"text":"and I'm one of the people that thinks that Tina Brown"},{"time":71000,"text":"was great for bringing photos to the New Yorker,"},{"time":73000,"text":"because this photo completely rocked my world."},{"time":75000,"text":"I became obsessed with the object --"},{"time":77000,"text":"not just the beautiful photograph itself,"},{"time":79000,"text":"and the color, the shallow depth of field, the detail that's visible,"},{"time":82000,"text":"the wire you can see on the beak there"},{"time":84000,"text":"that the conservator used to put this skeleton together --"},{"time":87000,"text":"there's an entire story here."},{"time":89000,"text":"And I thought to myself,"},{"time":91000,"text":"wouldn't it be great"},{"time":93000,"text":"if I had my own dodo skeleton?"},{"time":96000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99000,"text":"I want to point out here at this point that"},{"time":102000,"text":"I've spent my life obsessed"},{"time":104000,"text":"by objects and the stories that they tell,"},{"time":107000,"text":"and this was the very latest one."},{"time":109000,"text":"So I began looking around for --"},{"time":111000,"text":"to see if anyone sold a kit,"},{"time":113000,"text":"some kind of model that I could get,"},{"time":115000,"text":"and I found lots of reference material, lots of lovely pictures."},{"time":118000,"text":"No dice: no dodo skeleton for me. But the damage had been done."},{"time":122000,"text":"I had saved a few hundred photos of dodo skeletons"},{"time":124000,"text":"into my \"Creative Projects\" folder --"},{"time":126000,"text":"it's a repository for my brain, everything that I could possibly be interested in."},{"time":129000,"text":"Any time I have an internet connection,"},{"time":131000,"text":"there's a sluice of stuff moving into there,"},{"time":134000,"text":"everything from beautiful rings to cockpit photos."},{"time":138000,"text":"The key that the Marquis du Lafayette sent to George Washington"},{"time":141000,"text":"to celebrate the storming of the Bastille."},{"time":143000,"text":"Russian nuclear launch key:"},{"time":144000,"text":"The one on the top is the picture of the one I found on eBay;"},{"time":146000,"text":"the one on the bottom is the one I made for myself,"},{"time":149000,"text":"because I couldn't afford the one on eBay."},{"time":151000,"text":"Storm trooper costumes. Maps of Middle Earth --"},{"time":154000,"text":"that's one I hand-drew myself. There's the dodo skeleton folder."},{"time":156000,"text":"This folder has 17,000 photos --"},{"time":158000,"text":"over 20 gigabytes of information --"},{"time":160000,"text":"and it's growing constantly."},{"time":162000,"text":"And one day, a couple of weeks later, it might have been"},{"time":165000,"text":"maybe a year later, I was in the art store with my kids,"},{"time":167000,"text":"and I was buying some clay tools -- we were going to have a craft day."},{"time":170000,"text":"I bought some Super Sculpeys, some armature wire, some various materials."},{"time":173000,"text":"And I looked down at this Sculpey, and I thought,"},{"time":175000,"text":"maybe,"},{"time":177000,"text":"yeah, maybe I could make my own dodo skull."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"I should point out at this time -- I'm not a sculptor;"},{"time":183000,"text":"I'm a hard-edged model maker."},{"time":185000,"text":"You give me a drawing, you give me a prop to replicate,"},{"time":188000,"text":"you give me a crane, scaffolding, parts from \"Star Wars\" --"},{"time":191000,"text":"especially parts from \"Star Wars\" --"},{"time":193000,"text":"I can do this stuff all day long."},{"time":195000,"text":"It's exactly how I made my living for 15 years."},{"time":197000,"text":"But you give me something like this --"},{"time":200000,"text":"my friend Mike Murnane sculpted this;"},{"time":202000,"text":"it's a maquette for \"Star Wars, Episode Two\" --"},{"time":204000,"text":"this is not my thing --"},{"time":206000,"text":"this is something other people do -- dragons, soft things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"However, I felt like I had looked at enough photos of dodo skulls"},{"time":213000,"text":"to actually be able to"},{"time":215000,"text":"understand the topology and perhaps replicate it --"},{"time":218000,"text":"I mean, it couldn't be that difficult."},{"time":220000,"text":"So, I started looking at the best photos I could find."},{"time":223000,"text":"I grabbed all the reference,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and I found this lovely piece of reference."},{"time":227000,"text":"This is someone selling this on eBay;"},{"time":229000,"text":"it was clearly a womanâ€™s hand, hopefully a woman's hand."},{"time":232000,"text":"Assuming it was roughly the size of my wife's hand,"},{"time":234000,"text":"I made some measurements of her thumb, and I scaled them out to the size of the skull."},{"time":237000,"text":"I blew it up to the actual size, and I began using that,"},{"time":240000,"text":"along with all the other reference that I had, comparing it to it"},{"time":242000,"text":"as size reference for figuring out exactly how big the beak should be,"},{"time":245000,"text":"exactly how long, etc."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247000,"text":"And over a few hours, I eventually achieved"},{"time":250000,"text":"what was actually a pretty reasonable dodo skull. And I didn't mean to continue, I --"},{"time":253000,"text":"it's kind of like, you know, you can only clean a super messy room"},{"time":256000,"text":"by picking up one thing at a time; you can't think about the totality."},{"time":259000,"text":"I wasn't thinking about a dodo skeleton;"},{"time":261000,"text":"I just noticed that as I finished this skull,"},{"time":263000,"text":"the armature wire that I had been used to holding it up"},{"time":265000,"text":"was sticking out of the back just where a spine would be."},{"time":267000,"text":"And one of the other things I'd been interested in and obsessed with over the years"},{"time":270000,"text":"is spines and skeletons, having collected a couple of hundred."},{"time":273000,"text":"I actually understood the mechanics"},{"time":275000,"text":"of vertebrae enough to kind of start to imitate them."},{"time":278000,"text":"And so button by button,"},{"time":280000,"text":"vertebrae by vertebrae, I built my way down."},{"time":283000,"text":"And actually, by the end of the day, I had a reasonable skull,"},{"time":286000,"text":"a moderately good vertebrae and half of a pelvis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"And again, I kept on going, looking for more reference,"},{"time":293000,"text":"every bit of reference I could find -- drawings, beautiful photos."},{"time":296000,"text":"This guy -- I love this guy! He put a dodo leg bones on a scanner"},{"time":299000,"text":"with a ruler."},{"time":301000,"text":"This is the kind of accuracy that I wanted,"},{"time":303000,"text":"and I"},{"time":305000,"text":"replicated every last bone and put it in."},{"time":307000,"text":"And after about six weeks,"},{"time":310000,"text":"I finished, painted, mounted"},{"time":313000,"text":"my own dodo skeleton."},{"time":318000,"text":"You can see that I even made a museum label for it"},{"time":320000,"text":"that includes a brief history of the dodo."},{"time":322000,"text":"And TAP Plastics made me -- although I didn't photograph it --"},{"time":324000,"text":"a museum vitrine."},{"time":326000,"text":"I don't have the room for this in my house,"},{"time":328000,"text":"but I had to finish what I had started."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331000,"text":"And this actually represented kind of a sea change to me."},{"time":334000,"text":"Again, like I said, my life has been about"},{"time":336000,"text":"being fascinated by objects and the stories that they tell,"},{"time":338000,"text":"and also making them for myself, obtaining them,"},{"time":341000,"text":"appreciating them and diving into them."},{"time":344000,"text":"And in this folder, \"Creative Projects,\""},{"time":346000,"text":"there are tons of projects that I'm currently working on,"},{"time":349000,"text":"projects that I've already worked on, things that I might want to work on some day,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and things that I may just want to find and buy and have"},{"time":355000,"text":"and look at and touch."},{"time":357000,"text":"But now there was potentially this new category of things"},{"time":360000,"text":"that I could sculpt"},{"time":362000,"text":"that was different, that I -- you know,"},{"time":364000,"text":"I have my own R2D2, but that's --"},{"time":366000,"text":"honestly, relative to sculpting, to me, that's easy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369000,"text":"And so I went back and looked through my \"Creative Projects\" folder,"},{"time":372000,"text":"and I happened across the Maltese Falcon."},{"time":376000,"text":"Now, this is funny for me:"},{"time":379000,"text":"to fall in love with an object from a Hammett novel,"},{"time":382000,"text":"because if it's true that the world is divided into two types of people,"},{"time":384000,"text":"Chandler people and Hammett people, I am absolutely a Chandler person."},{"time":387000,"text":"But in this case,"},{"time":389000,"text":"it's not about the author, it's not about the book or the movie or the story,"},{"time":393000,"text":"it's about the object in and of itself."},{"time":395000,"text":"And in this case, this object is --"},{"time":398000,"text":"plays on a host of levels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"First of all, there's the object in the world."},{"time":403000,"text":"This is the \"Kniphausen Hawk.\""},{"time":405000,"text":"It is a ceremonial pouring vessel"},{"time":407000,"text":"made around 1700 for a Swedish Count,"},{"time":411000,"text":"and it is very likely the object from which"},{"time":413000,"text":"Hammett drew his inspiration for the Maltese Falcon."},{"time":416000,"text":"Then there is the fictional bird, the one that Hammett created for the book."},{"time":419000,"text":"Built out of words, it is the engine"},{"time":421000,"text":"that drives the plot of his book and also the movie,"},{"time":424000,"text":"in which another object is created:"},{"time":426000,"text":"a prop that has to represent the thing that Hammett created out of words,"},{"time":429000,"text":"inspired by the Kniphausen Hawk, and this represents the falcon in the movie."},{"time":433000,"text":"And then there is this fourth level, which is"},{"time":435000,"text":"a whole new object in the world:"},{"time":437000,"text":"the prop made for the movie, the representative of the thing,"},{"time":440000,"text":"becomes, in its own right,"},{"time":442000,"text":"a whole other thing,"},{"time":444000,"text":"a whole new object of desire."}]},{"cues":[{"time":446000,"text":"And so now it was time to do some research."},{"time":448000,"text":"I actually had done some research"},{"time":450000,"text":"a few years before -- it's why the folder was there."},{"time":452000,"text":"I'd bought a replica, a really crappy replica,"},{"time":454000,"text":"of the Maltese Falcon on eBay,"},{"time":456000,"text":"and had downloaded enough pictures to actually"},{"time":458000,"text":"have some reasonable reference."},{"time":460000,"text":"But I discovered,"},{"time":462000,"text":"in researching further,"},{"time":464000,"text":"really wanting precise reference, that"},{"time":467000,"text":"one of the original lead birds"},{"time":469000,"text":"had been sold at Christie's in 1994,"},{"time":471000,"text":"and so I contacted an antiquarian bookseller"},{"time":474000,"text":"who had the original Christie's catalogue,"},{"time":476000,"text":"and in it I found this magnificent picture,"},{"time":478000,"text":"which included a size reference."},{"time":480000,"text":"I was able to scan the picture, blow it up to exactly full size."}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"I found other reference. Avi [Ara] Chekmayan,"},{"time":486000,"text":"a New Jersey editor, actually found this"},{"time":488000,"text":"resin Maltese Falcon"},{"time":490000,"text":"at a flea market in 1991,"},{"time":493000,"text":"although it took him five years"},{"time":495000,"text":"to authenticate this bird to"},{"time":497000,"text":"the auctioneers' specifications,"},{"time":499000,"text":"because there was a lot of controversy about it."},{"time":501000,"text":"It was made out of resin, which wasn't a common material for movie props"},{"time":503000,"text":"about the time the movie was made."},{"time":505000,"text":"It's funny to me that it took a while to authenticate it,"},{"time":507000,"text":"because I can see it compared to this thing,"},{"time":509000,"text":"and I can tell you -- it's real, it's the real thing,"},{"time":511000,"text":"it's made from the exact same mold that this one is."},{"time":514000,"text":"In this one, because the auction was actually so controversial,"},{"time":517000,"text":"Profiles in History, the auction house that sold this --"},{"time":519000,"text":"I think in 1995 for about 100,000 dollars --"},{"time":521000,"text":"they actually included -- you can see here on the bottom --"},{"time":524000,"text":"not just a front elevation, but also"},{"time":526000,"text":"a side, rear"},{"time":528000,"text":"and other side elevation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530000,"text":"So now, I had all the topology I needed"},{"time":533000,"text":"to replicate the Maltese Falcon."},{"time":535000,"text":"What do they do, how do you start something like that? I really don't know."},{"time":538000,"text":"So what I did was, again, like I did with the dodo skull,"},{"time":540000,"text":"I blew all my reference up to full size,"},{"time":543000,"text":"and then I began cutting out the negatives and using"},{"time":545000,"text":"those templates as shape references."},{"time":547000,"text":"So I took Sculpey, and I built a big block of it,"},{"time":549000,"text":"and I passed it through until, you know, I got the right profiles."},{"time":552000,"text":"And then slowly, feather by feather, detail by detail,"},{"time":555000,"text":"I worked out and achieved --"},{"time":557000,"text":"working in front of the television and Super Sculpey --"},{"time":559000,"text":"here's me sitting next to my wife --"},{"time":561000,"text":"it's the only picture I took of the entire process."},{"time":564000,"text":"As I moved through, I achieved"},{"time":566000,"text":"a very reasonable facsimile of the Maltese Falcon."},{"time":568000,"text":"But again, I am not a sculptor,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"and so I don't know a lot of the tricks, like,"},{"time":573000,"text":"I don't know how my friend Mike gets beautiful, shiny surfaces with his Sculpey;"},{"time":576000,"text":"I certainly wasn't able to get it."},{"time":578000,"text":"So, I went down to my shop,"},{"time":580000,"text":"and I molded it and I cast it in resin,"},{"time":583000,"text":"because in the resin, then, I could absolutely get the glass smooth finished."},{"time":586000,"text":"Now there's a lot of ways to fill and get yourself a nice smooth finish."},{"time":589000,"text":"My preference is about 70 coats of this --"},{"time":592000,"text":"matte black auto primer."},{"time":594000,"text":"I spray it on for about three or four days, it drips to hell,"},{"time":597000,"text":"but it allows me a really, really nice gentle sanding surface"},{"time":600000,"text":"and I can get it glass-smooth."},{"time":602000,"text":"Oh, finishing up with triple-zero steel wool."},{"time":604000,"text":"Now, the great thing about getting it to this point was that"},{"time":607000,"text":"because in the movie, when they finally bring out the bird at the end,"},{"time":609000,"text":"and they place it on the table, they actually spin it."},{"time":612000,"text":"So I was able to actually"},{"time":614000,"text":"screen-shot and freeze-frame to make sure."},{"time":617000,"text":"And I'm following all the light kicks on this thing and making sure that as I'm holding the light"},{"time":620000,"text":"in the same position, I'm getting the same type of reflection on it --"},{"time":623000,"text":"that's the level of detail I'm going into this thing."},{"time":626000,"text":"I ended up with this: my Maltese Falcon."},{"time":629000,"text":"And it's beautiful. And I can state with authority"},{"time":631000,"text":"at this point in time, when I'd finished it,"},{"time":633000,"text":"of all of the replicas out there -- and there is a few --"},{"time":636000,"text":"this is by far the most accurate"},{"time":638000,"text":"representation of the original Maltese Falcon"},{"time":640000,"text":"than anyone has sculpted. Now the original one, I should tell you,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":643000,"text":"is sculpted by a guy named Fred Sexton."},{"time":645000,"text":"This is where it gets weird."},{"time":648000,"text":"Fred Sexton was a friend of this guy, George Hodel."},{"time":651000,"text":"Terrifying guy -- agreed by many to be the killer"},{"time":653000,"text":"of the Black Dahlia."},{"time":655000,"text":"Now, James Ellroy believes"},{"time":657000,"text":"that Fred Sexton, the sculptor of the Maltese Falcon,"},{"time":660000,"text":"killed James Elroy's mother."},{"time":662000,"text":"I'll go you one stranger than that: In 1974,"},{"time":665000,"text":"during the production of a weird comedy sequel to \"The Maltese Falcon,\""},{"time":668000,"text":"called \"The Black Bird,\" starring George Segal,"},{"time":670000,"text":"the Los Angeles County Museum of Art"},{"time":672000,"text":"had a plaster original of the Maltese Falcon --"},{"time":674000,"text":"one of the original six plasters, I think, made for the movie --"},{"time":677000,"text":"stolen out of the museum. A lot of people thought"},{"time":679000,"text":"it was a publicity stunt for the movie."},{"time":681000,"text":"John's Grill, which actually"},{"time":683000,"text":"is seen briefly in \"The Maltese Falcon,\""},{"time":685000,"text":"is still a viable San Francisco eatery,"},{"time":687000,"text":"counted amongst its regular customers Elisha Cook,"},{"time":689000,"text":"who played Wilmer Cook in the movie,"},{"time":691000,"text":"and he gave them"},{"time":693000,"text":"one of his original plasters of the Maltese Falcon."},{"time":696000,"text":"And they had it in their cabinet for about 15 years,"},{"time":699000,"text":"until it got stolen"},{"time":701000,"text":"in January of 2007."},{"time":704000,"text":"It would seem that the object of desire"},{"time":706000,"text":"only comes into its own by disappearing repeatedly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"So here I had this Falcon,"},{"time":711000,"text":"and it was lovely. It looked really great,"},{"time":713000,"text":"the light worked on it really well,"},{"time":715000,"text":"it was better than anything that I could achieve"},{"time":717000,"text":"or obtain out in the world."},{"time":719000,"text":"But there was a problem. And the problem was that:"},{"time":723000,"text":"I wanted the entirety of the object,"},{"time":725000,"text":"I wanted the weight behind the object."},{"time":728000,"text":"This thing was made of resin and it was too light."},{"time":730000,"text":"There's this group online that I frequent."},{"time":732000,"text":"It's a group of prop crazies just like me"},{"time":735000,"text":"called the Replica Props Forum, and it's people who trade,"},{"time":737000,"text":"make and travel in information about movie props."},{"time":740000,"text":"And it turned out that one of the guys there,"},{"time":742000,"text":"a friend of mine that I never actually met,"},{"time":745000,"text":"but befriended through some prop deals, was the manager of a local foundry."},{"time":747000,"text":"He took my master Falcon pattern,"},{"time":750000,"text":"he actually did lost wax casting"},{"time":752000,"text":"in bronze for me,"},{"time":754000,"text":"and this is the bronze I got back."},{"time":756000,"text":"And this is, after some acid etching, the one that I ended up with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758000,"text":"And this thing, it's deeply, deeply satisfying to me."},{"time":761000,"text":"Here, I'm going to put it out there,"},{"time":763000,"text":"later on tonight, and"},{"time":767000,"text":"I want you to pick it up and handle it."},{"time":771000,"text":"You want to know"},{"time":774000,"text":"how obsessed I am. This project's only for me,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and yet I went so far as to buy on eBay"},{"time":779000,"text":"a 1941 Chinese San Francisco-based newspaper,"},{"time":782000,"text":"in order so that the bird could properly be wrapped ..."},{"time":786000,"text":"like it is in the movie."},{"time":788000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":792000,"text":"Yeah, I know!"},{"time":794000,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"},{"time":799000,"text":"There you can see, it's weighing in at 27 and a half pounds."},{"time":802000,"text":"That's half the weight of my dog, Huxley."}]},{"cues":[{"time":806000,"text":"But there's a problem."},{"time":809000,"text":"Now, here's the most recent progression of Falcons."},{"time":812000,"text":"On the far left is a piece of crap -- a replica I bought on eBay."},{"time":815000,"text":"There's my somewhat ruined Sculpey Falcon,"},{"time":817000,"text":"because I had to get it back out of the mold. There's my first casting,"},{"time":820000,"text":"there's my master and there's my bronze."},{"time":822000,"text":"There's a thing that happens when you mold and cast things,"},{"time":825000,"text":"which is that every time you throw it into silicone and cast it in resin,"},{"time":827000,"text":"you lose a little bit of volume, you lose a little bit of size."},{"time":830000,"text":"And when I held my bronze one up against my Sculpey one,"},{"time":833000,"text":"it was shorter by three-quarters of an inch."},{"time":836000,"text":"Yeah, no, really, this was like aah --"},{"time":840000,"text":"why didn't I remember this?"},{"time":842000,"text":"Why didn't I start and make it bigger?"},{"time":845000,"text":"So what do I do? I figure I have two options."},{"time":848000,"text":"One, I can fire a freaking laser at it,"},{"time":851000,"text":"which I have already done,"},{"time":853000,"text":"to do a 3D scan -- there's a 3D scan of this Falcon."},{"time":855000,"text":"I had figured out the exact amount of shrinkage I achieved"},{"time":858000,"text":"going from a wax master to a bronze master"},{"time":860000,"text":"and blown this up big enough to make"},{"time":862000,"text":"a 3D lithography master of this,"},{"time":864000,"text":"which I will polish, then I will send to the mold maker"},{"time":867000,"text":"and then I will have it done in bronze. Or:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":870000,"text":"There are several people who own originals,"},{"time":872000,"text":"and I have been attempting to contact them and reach them,"},{"time":875000,"text":"hoping that they will let me spend a few minutes"},{"time":878000,"text":"in the presence of one of the real birds, maybe to take a picture,"},{"time":880000,"text":"or even to pull out the hand-held laser scanner"},{"time":883000,"text":"that I happen to own that fits inside a cereal box,"},{"time":886000,"text":"and could maybe, without even touching their bird, I swear,"},{"time":888000,"text":"get a perfect 3D scan. And I'm even willing to sign pages"},{"time":891000,"text":"saying that I'll never let anyone else have it, except for me in my office, I promise."},{"time":894000,"text":"I'll give them one if they want it."},{"time":897000,"text":"And then, maybe, then I'll achieve the end of this exercise."},{"time":900000,"text":"But really, if we're all going to be honest with ourselves,"},{"time":902000,"text":"I have to admit that achieving the end of the exercise"},{"time":905000,"text":"was never the point of the exercise to begin with, was it."},{"time":908000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}